(10795, 827, 'descriptions', 'Many people find gambling fun and harmless and learn how to control their urges. Yet, <a href=\"https://www.dia.govt.nz/pubforms.nsf/URL/ProblemGamblingFactsFinal.pdf/$file/ProblemGamblingFactsFinal.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">a small percentage of New Zealand gamblers</a> find it difficult to cope with temptation and halt on time. And the detection of the condition is not always easy and straightforward.\r\n\r\nGambling addiction is a serious mental condition. It preoccupies the mind of pathological gamblers. They find it hard to set limits and often chase losses to infinity. It can reduce the quality of life and harm or even ruin relationships. Problem gambling can deteriorate any aspect of your health. And it has a domino effect. So, always pursue responsible gambling and stay alert and informed.\r\n\r\nOur job is always to keep you up-to-date and guide you on the path to responsible gambling. This article will elaborate on and provide insight into the following topics:'),
