(10925, 827, 'additional_blocks_1_text', '<a href=\"https://www.msd.govt.nz/about-msd-and-our-work/publications-resources/journals-and-magazines/social-policy-journal/spj21/21-gambling-in-new-zealand-pages178-201.html#TheNatureofGambling4\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">The nature of gambling addiction is complex</a>, with no unique reason that stimulates such behaviour. In short, there isn\'t just one cause responsible for being hooked to gambling. Several factors are inter-related and lead to the formation of addictive habits. The worst scenario is related to the inability of some NZ players to control their online gambling behaviour.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><b>Biological causes.</b>\r\nWe are all different and inclined to activities that entertain and fascinate us. Our brain is in pursuit of happy hormones and seeks pleasurable activities to keep it stimulated and excited. Compulsive gambling is also related to genetics and personal traits. Thus, some risk factors can be inherited.</li>\r\n 	<li><b>Psychological causes.</b>\r\nPsychological factors play a key role in the formation of the distorted reality gamblers perceive. The primary reasons include the belief that such activities reduce stress levels. Players hope to overcome boredom. The pleasurable feelings coming from winnings also influence this process. Hence, the coping skills of addicts are poor.</li>\r\n 	<li><b>Socio-cultural causes.</b>\r\nIt is in our nature to interact with people and feel welcomed and accepted. Since many <a href=\"/safe-casinos/\">NZ casino sites</a> offer a pleasant social atmosphere, Kiwis feel understood in the community. Gambling levels can also increase if family members and close friends approve of regular gambling and practice it regularly.</li>\r\n 	<li><b>Spiritual causes.</b>\r\nSome people believe in higher powers and omnipotent Gods, and that deters them from gambling activities. Others New Zealanders personal sets of values and are detached from religion. It is easier for people that neglect universal laws to dive deeper into gambling waters.</li>\r\n</ul>'),
