(10943, 827, 'additional_blocks_2_text', 'There\'s no straightforward set of trails that shows us who is gambling in addictive ways. The paramount step is first to acknowledge the signs and symptoms and then seek plausible solutions. This is not always easy and obvious. And the circle is difficult to break. Below are the most <a href=\"https://www.begambleaware.org/gambling-problems/signs-to-look-out-for/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">common signs that Kiwis are getting involved in gambling increasingly</a>.\r\n\r\n<u><b>Signs:</b></u>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><b>Making money this way.</b>\r\nWhat leads to <a href=\"/real-money-casinos/\">real money gambling</a> is the desperate need for instant cash. The idea that you\'ll climb up the social ladder in no time is compelling. Plus, NZ gamblers believe this will settle all their problems, and they\'ll break even. It\'s easy, and you only need some luck.</li>\r\n 	<li><b>Keeping your activity as a secret.</b>\r\nAddictive gamblers feel they must keep their hobby secretive. Only then has the activity crossed the limits of responsible play. If you\'re late and absent-minded more often than not, there\'s a real issue with gambling. Keeping whereabouts in secret means that you feel something is wrong with your ways.</li>\r\n 	<li><b>Taking loans to gamble.</b>\r\nYou gamble even when you cannot afford it. And then switch to <a href=\"/paypal-casinos/\">online gambling with PayPal credit</a> or <a href=\"/credit-card-casinos/\">credit card casinos</a>. Or you\'ve come to the point when you consider taking loans to cover debts. Don\'t neglect this ominous sign as coming back to the right track is getting harder.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<u><b>Symptoms:</b></u>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><b>Emotional.</b>\r\nThe apparent symptoms include exaggerated anxiety and depression. Addicted players get easily upset and often feel sad. Some Kiwi players even have suicidal thoughts. Losing all your money on gambling is disappointing. It can make people feel hopeless and end their life deliberately.</li>\r\n 	<li><b>Physical.</b>\r\nWhen the desperation phase comes in, players no longer control the situation. Negative feelings reflect on physical health, and this is extremely dangerous. Self-inflicting harm is the worst-case scenario. Sleep deprivation is another aspect that must be considered. Weight variations, pale skin, and acnes are specific indicators.</li>\r\n</ul>'),
