(10961, 827, 'additional_blocks_3_text', 'The best way to tackle gambling addiction is to prevent it from the start. Dealing with the consequences is harder than being self-aware beforehand. There is nothing wrong with gambling for a short time. But when gambling occupies your entire time, and you cannot control yourself, it\'s time to act. Take our professional tips to stay safe when playing online.\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li><b>Choose trusted casino brands.</b>\r\nSafe online casinos for Kiwis can spare you from much trouble. They never let you fall into addictive playing. Reputable NZ casinos take care of your time spent on gambling and the size of losses suffered. Your safety should be a top priority of sites where you gamble.</li>\r\n 	<li><b>Don\'t chase losses.</b>\r\nThis is the worst gambling strategy that gets you into the vicious circle of never quitting. Trying to get any money lost will get you deeper into the black hole of debts. Drop the idea that your luck must change soon. Also, don\'t play higher stakes once you\'ve lost.</li>\r\n 	<li><b>Set and limit your budget.</b>\r\nThis is genuinely viable with any <a href=\"/low-deposit-casinos/\">low deposit casino</a>. A small deposit means it\'s easier for you to restrain your spending. Also, quit playing when you reach your limits, even if you are winning. The idea that your luck will serve you longer can indulge you exceed the rigorous limits.</li>\r\n 	<li><b>Avoid gambling under the influence.</b>\r\nAvoid playing at New Zealand online casinos under the influence of alcohol or drugs. This will diminish your reasoning, and you might place higher bets than planned. Drugs make you overestimate your abilities. Alcohol makes you aggressive, and you can inflict harm to yourself or others around you.</li>\r\n 	<li><b>Read bonus terms.</b>\r\n<a href=\"/gambling-sites/\">Kiwi gambling sites</a> offer different bonuses to players. Meaning, you must read the terms of offered bonuses before using them thoroughly. Some bonuses apply to certain games in specific periods only. Others are available after you make a certain deposit.</li>\r\n 	<li><b>Learn the rules before playing for real money.</b>\r\nDon\'t skip this step in pursuit of excitement. Get familiar with any rules and regulations imposed by the Kiwi online casino. Check the wagering requirements, too. If you take a closer look at game specifics, you\'ll avoid losing money out of misunderstandings. Protect yourself by being knowledgeable.</li>\r\n 	<li><b>Test demo games or use free credit deals.</b>\r\nTop-notch New Zealand casinos recommend playing demo games to educate players on the process. No deposit casino bonuses are also available to enable gamblers to check the variety and quality of games. Once you familiarize yourself with the rules, it\'ll be easier to decide if that\'s what you wanted.</li>\r\n</ol>'),
