(11014, 827, '_additional_blocks_6_casino_taxonomy', 'field_5ce26afd55a81'),
(11015, 827, 'additional_blocks_6_text', 'Today, children have unlimited access to almost anything offered online. With violence, drugs, and bullying on the rise, we tend to oversee gambling. Yet, if more inventive, minors can log in with their parents\' data without being detected. It\'s essential to block any gambling site from your children\'s devices.\r\n\r\nIt is an indisputable fact that more young New Zealanders start gambling nowadays. They are more easily affected if a family member is a gambler. This way, the attitude or minors towards gambling is distorted. And kids are more prone to developing harmful addictions.\r\n\r\nSo, it\'s essential to detach and prevent kids from gambling at an earlier age. Even if you are a gambling fan, specific tips can help you keep your kids away from gambling. Never leave your PC unattended when gambling online and make sure you have a password-protected profile. Teach them the risks and perils of gambling.\r\n\r\nChildren in families with gambling problems are in great danger, too. These kids run the risk of being tormented and neglected. They might suffer abuse or other forms of domestic violence. Even if this is not the case, they may develop depression or substance abuse later in life.'),
