(11055, 827, 'additional_blocks_9_questions_0_question', '🤔 What is gambling addiction?'),
(11056, 827, '_additional_blocks_9_questions_0_question', 'field_6049f57442219'),
(11057, 827, 'additional_blocks_9_questions_0_answer', 'Gambling addiction is a human vice that can lead to financial collapse. Compulsive gambling is a condition that urges players to continue betting. Regardless of the consequences or the impact of enormous losses, addicts never stop. Compulsive gamblers cannot control their desire to gamble, so it\'s crucial to stop at the early warning signs.'),
(11058, 827, '_additional_blocks_9_questions_0_answer', 'field_6049f5744226b'),
(11059, 827, 'additional_blocks_9_questions_1_question', '😷 Is gambling addiction a disease?'),
(11060, 827, '_additional_blocks_9_questions_1_question', 'field_6049f57442219'),
(11061, 827, 'additional_blocks_9_questions_1_answer', 'Gambling addiction is considered a mental health disorder. It\'s an impulse control disorder, and it requires immediate help and constant treatment. Many gamblers suffer reoccurring conditions. And the addiction is progressive with many psychological, physical, and social repercussions. Worse, it frequently co-occurs with other substance abuse problems. Since its harmful consequences are enormous, many countries classify gambling addiction as a public health concern.'),
(11062, 827, '_additional_blocks_9_questions_1_answer', 'field_6049f5744226b'),
(11063, 827, 'additional_blocks_9_questions_2_question', '🛑 Why can\'t I stop gambling?'),
(11064, 827, '_additional_blocks_9_questions_2_question', 'field_6049f57442219'),
(11065, 827, 'additional_blocks_9_questions_2_answer', 'Gamblers tend to disregard the addiction aspect of their hobby. But, once you realize you\'ve come too far with gambling, it\'s time to reach a decision. Staying true to your choices is another issue. First, talk to close friends or family. Practice visualization of what would happen if you lose again. Take a day-by-day approach. If everything fails, seek treatment.'),
(11066, 827, '_additional_blocks_9_questions_2_answer', 'field_6049f5744226b'),
(11067, 827, 'additional_blocks_9_questions_3_question', '🧪 How to test if I\'m gambling-addicted?'),
(11068, 827, '_additional_blocks_9_questions_3_question', 'field_6049f57442219'),
(11069, 827, 'additional_blocks_9_questions_3_answer', 'The good thing is that you can find many gambling addiction tests online. Those are free, instant, and anonymous for anyone to take. Tests will tell you whether you have a gambling issue or you\'re playing reasonably. Such online assessments can also point out the stadium at which your addiction stands. This is the first step towards admitting to yourself that you\'ve gone too far. Treatment centres use similar tests.'),
(11070, 827, '_additional_blocks_9_questions_3_answer', 'field_6049f5744226b'),
(11071, 827, 'additional_blocks_9_questions_4_question', '🧠 I probably have a gambling problem. What should I do?'),
(11072, 827, '_additional_blocks_9_questions_4_question', 'field_6049f57442219'),
(11073, 827, 'additional_blocks_9_questions_4_answer', 'Seek help right away. Consult any of the support platforms outlined here. Be persistent in your intentions to quit or restrict your gambling activities. Make a plan and stick to it regardless of moments of weakness. We suggest you sign up for a self-exclusion scheme. It will ban you from accessing online casinos for a specified period.'),
